question_title: Caveats of analyzing program performance  True or False

question_content.description:
### Problem20


- Instruction time: Each instruction always takes the same amount of time. (_____(0)\___)
- Nondominant inner loop: The inner loop not always dominates.  (_____(1)\___)
- System considerations: What is happening at this moment in your computer will never be reproduced again and java are just a part of it, which may lead to an significantly affect to performance. (_____(2)\___)
- Strong dependence on input values: The running time of program should always depend primarily on the problem size. (_____(3)\___)
